multiflexi (2.3.3) UNRELEASED; urgency=medium

  [ vitex ]
  * Add Task API: GET /tasks.{suffix} and GET /task/{taskId}.{suffix}
  * Add Task schema to openapi-schema.yaml
  * Job schema: add task_id field
  * Add missing tags (credential, credential_type, topic) so the
    generator produces dedicated API classes instead of silently folding
    these operations into DefaultApi.
  * Split 5 dual-tagged operations (getUserRoles, setUserRoles,
    listCompanyUsers, assignUserToCompany, unassignUserFromCompany) into
    single user-role/user-company tags; dual tags caused the generator
    to emit duplicate, ambiguous route registrations for the same path
    pointing at two different classes.

  [ CyberVitexus ]
  * Fix App.exitCodes schema: was an array missing the code key (lossy),
    now an object keyed by exit code (additionalProperties:
    ExitCodeDetail), matching what the server already emits.
  * Fix apps.{suffix}, jobs.{suffix}, runtemplates.{suffix}: spec declared
    a JSON array, server has always returned an object keyed by record
    id; corrected the spec to match, so generated clients stop failing
    to deserialize these list responses.
  * Fix JobApi::getJobById/listJobs wrapping responses in an extra
    "job"/"jobs" key, unlike every other list/by-id endpoint (App,
    RunTemplate); removed the wrapper for consistency.
  * Fix AppApi::getAppById: environment/exitCodes now always encode as a
    JSON object, even when empty or when exit codes happen to be
    numbered sequentially from 0 (PHP's json_encode() otherwise emits a
    JSON array in both cases).
  * Fix App.tags schema: declared as an array of Tag objects, but there
    is no Tag entity in the implementation -- it has always been a
    comma-separated string, same as the deprecated topics field.
    Corrected the spec to type: string.
  * Fix AppApi::listApps: `enabled` came back as raw int (0/1) from
    getAll(), unlike getAppById() which casts it to bool via
    loadFromSQL()/getData(); cast explicitly so both endpoints match the
    spec's `enabled: boolean`.
  * Fix Job.launched_by/env schema: declared as string, but the server
    has always returned an integer user id and an unserialized object
    respectively. Corrected the spec to match.
  * Fix RuntemplateApi success/fail: empty case returned '' (matches
    neither the spec's nullable-object type nor any sane client model);
    now returns null. Non-empty case now force-cast to object so
    json_encode() can't emit a JSON array for action maps.
  * Fix RuntemplateApi `active`/`prepared`: neither listRuntemplates()
    nor getRunTemplateById() cast these tinyint columns to bool
    (getData() doesn't do it either, unlike Application's `enabled`);
    cast explicitly in both, preserving null for `prepared` (nullable).

 -- CyberVitexus <cybervitexus@gmail.com>  Wed, 15 Jul 2026 08:21:51 +0200

